values.content:
=Analyze the meeting transcript below and return exactly this JSON structure. Do not deviate from it.

{
  "meeting_title": "",
  "executive_summary": "",
  "high_level_objectives": [
    { "title": "", "description": "" }
  ],
  "action_items": [
    { "task": "", "owner": "", "due_date": "", "priority": "" }
  ],
  "next_steps": [
    { "step": "", "owner": "", "timing": "" }
  ],
  "risks_or_open_questions": []
}

FIELD RULES:
- meeting_title: short title inferred from the discussion topic.
- executive_summary: 80–140 words, business-ready language, no bullet points.
- high_level_objectives: exactly 3 items. Derive from discussion context if not explicit.
- action_items: exactly 3 items. Prioritize explicitly assigned tasks; derive if needed.
  - priority values: "high" | "medium" | "low"
  - due_date: ISO 8601 (YYYY-MM-DD) if stated, otherwise "unknown"
- next_steps: 3 to 5 items. Ordered by logical sequence.
- risks_or_open_questions: list unresolved issues or stated risks as plain strings. Empty array [] if none.

TRANSCRIPT:
{{ $json.transcript }}

